                                                    <p>Business process management (BPM) is a domain that employs multiple tools and methodologies to design, model, execute, monitor, and optimize business processes. A business process directs the actions of people, systems, information, and objects to achieve business results that support a corporate strategy.<br><br>The main focus of using a BPM is to establish a uniform, automated procedure for everyday transactions and human interactions. BPM enables the business to reduce costs by eliminating rework and increases team productivity.<br></p>
